{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"usefulItems":"bowl, rectangular casserole dish (25 x 16 cm), oven","id":"r124227","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-mn0zyguR720\/XZWez1SFYOI\/AAAAAAAAe6I\/BAM-4H91U6AvJLKRKCtu_2se8Cn9_rs5gCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_i9wx25G4zMzNm6lc.png","title":"Maple bread and butter pudding with walnut crumble","publishedAt":"2017-04-02T00:00:00Z","ingredients2":[{"content":"300 g sliced wholemeal bread (see Tips)"},{"content":"60 g butter, softened"},{"content":"80 g pitted prunes, cut into pieces"},{"content":"60 g walnuts"},{"content":"3 tsp Rapadura sugar (see Tips)"},{"content":"1 tsp ground cinnamon"},{"content":"1 tbsp self-raising flour"},{"content":"3 eggs"},{"content":"2 tbsp pure maple syrup, plus extra to serve"},{"content":"100 g pouring (whipping) cream"},{"content":"500 g milk"},{"content":"1 tsp natural vanilla extract"},{"content":"natural yoghurt or custard, to serve (optional)"}],"nutrition":{"protein":"12.7 g","fat":"28.1 g","uom":"per 1 portions","carbohydrates":"39.7 g","calories":"1989 kJ \/ 473 kcal"},"preparations2":[{"content":"Preheat oven to 160°C. Place a bowl onto mixing bowl lid and weigh bread into it. Set bowl aside. Place a separate bowl onto mixing bowl lid and weigh 40 g butter into it. Set bowl aside. Place a separate bowl onto mixing bowl lid and weigh prunes into it. Set bowl aside."},{"content":"Lightly spread each bread slice with reserved butter, then cut each bread slice into halves. Place bread into a deep-sided ovenproof dish (approx. 25 x 16 cm). Sprinkle reserved chopped prunes over bread and set aside."},{"content":"Place walnuts into mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 4<b>, until coarsley chopped."},{"content":"Add sugar, remaining 20 g butter, cinnamon and flour and combine <b>8 sec\/\/speed 4<b>. Crumble should be quite lumpy. Transfer into a bowl and set aside."},{"content":"Without cleaning mixing bowl, place eggs, syrup, cream, milk and vanilla into mixing bowl and mix <b>10 sec\/speed 4<b>, until smooth."},{"content":"Pour mixture over bread, coating every slice. Set aside to absorb for 15 minutes."},{"content":"Bake for 30 minutes (160°C). Remove pudding from oven, scatter with reserved crumble topping and bake for a further 15-20 minutes (160°C), or until golden and pudding has set."},{"content":"Allow to cool for 5-10 minutes, then drizzle with extra maple syrup if desired, and serve with yoghurt or custard (optional)."}],"hintsAndTricks":["For a lower-calorie option, you can leave out the cream and use 600 g milk.","If you prefer, you can replace the prunes with raisins or sultanas.","You can use whichever wholemeal or wholegrain bread you like for this pudding – multigrain and rye are also lovely. Choose a softer bread to allow the custard to properly absorb. If your loaf is unsliced, cut into 1 cm slices.","You can use your preferred brown sugar in this recipe – either regular brown sugar or a less refined option such as Rapadura sugar (Panela) or coconut sugar."],"basicInfo":["easy","25m","1h 30m","6 portions"]}